{"serial": "43024", "department_serial": 39, "code": "IM5020", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Special Topics in Innovation", "ch": "創新管理專題"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Su, Yea-Huey"], "ch": ["蘇雅惠"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["5", "6", "7"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "404"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "資訊管理學系", "en": "Department of Information Management"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 25, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程旨在啟發學生的創業家精神，培養其掌握創新管理的多元思維，並發展運用前沿科技推動創新的實務能力。課程聚焦於新興科技 (如生成式AI) 的應用潛力，透過跨領域合作與實戰專題，引領學生突破既有架構，設計出兼具創意與實用性的解決方案。課程亦鼓勵批判性與創造性思維的發展，並強化學生評估創新機會與應對不確定性的能力。期望學生能在快速變遷的科技環境中，提出前瞻性的創新提案，並具備因應動態產業變化與探索未知領域的視野與能力。", "en": "This course aims to inspire students‘ entrepreneurship, broaden their perspectives in innovation management, and develop practical abilities in leveraging frontier technologies for innovation. Emphasizing the potential of emerging technologies, such as generative AI, the curriculum engages students in interdisciplinary collaboration and hands-on projects to challenge existing frameworks and create innovative yet practical solutions. The course also encourages the development of critical and creative thinking, equipping students to assess innovation opportunities and navigate uncertainty effectively. Ultimately, students are expected to propose forward-thinking innovation strategies, adapt to rapidly evolving technological landscapes, and acquire the vision and capabilities to address dynamic industry changes and explore uncharted territories."}, "outline": {"ch": "單元一：演進中的創新理論\n本單元旨在啟發學生的創業精神，系統性地探索創新理論的歷史演進。通過強調創新理論的動態性與持續演化特質，幫助學生理解創新如何因應社會與科技環境的變遷，推動組織與社會的轉型，並展現創新的本質與持續進步的價值。\n單元二：新興科技與創新實踐\n聚焦於新興科技（如生成式AI與Agent機器人）的應用潛力，學生將以問題為導向進行團隊合作，探索如何運用新技術發展創新解決方案。\n單元三：跨域創新實驗\n鼓勵學生突破領域界限，設計並執行創新實驗，探索跨領域合作如何催生突破性的創新成果，並以實踐檢驗創意的可行性。", "en": "Unit 1: Evolutionary Innovation Theories\nThis unit aims to inspire students‘ entrepreneurship while systematically examining the historical evolution of innovation theories. By emphasizing the dynamic and continuously evolving nature of these theories, students will understand how innovation adapts to changing societal and technological contexts, drives organizational and societal transformation, and reflects the nature of innovation and continuous progress.\nUnit 2: Emerging Technologies and Innovation Practice\nThis unit focuses on the potential applications of emerging technologies, such as generative AI and agent robots. Students will participate in problem-oriented teamwork to explore how these technologies can be harnessed to develop innovative solutions.\nUnit 3: Interdisciplinary Innovation Experiments\nThis unit encourages students to break traditional disciplinary boundaries, design and implement innovation experiments, and investigate how interdisciplinary collaboration can foster breakthrough innovations. Students will also validate the feasibility of creative ideas through practical application."}, "textbook": {"ch": "上課公佈", "en": "To be announced"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "50%", "en": "50%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "上課公佈", "en": "To be announced"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "by appointment via email", "en": "by appointment via email"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "17+1", "en": "17+1"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "第18週：課程相關領域線上諮詢 (optional)", "en": "For Week 18, the instructor offers an optional online consultation session for students interested in diving deeper into related topics."}, "domain": {"ch": "商業智慧\n\n\n、\n\n\n商管知識", "en": "商業智慧\n\n\n、\n\n\n商管知識"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "原創性", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現", "其他"]}, {"competenci